      "playtime_at_review": 223,
      "review_text": "Haters are gonna hate; I like this game even more than \"Minecraft\".\r\n\r\nThis game has a lot of similarity to \"Ark: Survival Evolved\", but with monster catching game mechanics, among open-world survival craft video games.\r\n\r\nIS it a masterpiece? I honestly don't know, but it at least has POTENTIAL to get there! \r\n\r\nIs it a GREAT video game worth playing, IF you have a PC that's powerful enough? DEFINITELY! (P.S.; there are A LOT of adorable creatures in this game!)",
      "timestamp_created": 1774125938
    },
    {
      "review_id": "221313731",
      "author_steamid": "76561198010797965",
      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 0,
      "playtime_at_review": 1767,
      "review_text": "Palworld has a ton of depth in the building, crafting, and breeding dynamics. Tons to do, especially if you're one to like unguided open-world experiences. They've added a lot in the way of guidance, but it's still not what you'd consider a AAA story-driven experience a la Elder Scrolls or Fallout. It's still a ton of fun though, especially if you have friends to share a server with.",
